cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SI

This paper deals with language dynamics and statistical analysis of word usage in a large corpus of English fiction. The paper uses methods from natural language processing and machine learning to analyze the corpus, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of statistical methods to analyze the corpus, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries). Finally, the paper discusses the cultural and social implications of language evolution, which could place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
